.md","tags":[],"version":"current","sidebarPosition":2,"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":2},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"Overview of the Harmonisation Pipeline","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/"},"next":{"title":"Orientation of palindromic variants","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/Introduction/Orientation-of-palindromic-variants"}},{"id":"Introduction/Harmonising-the-variants","title":"Harmonising the variants","description":"Each variant is harmonised by aligning it with a reference datasetâ€”specifically, the Ensembl VCF reference. This process ensures allele consistency and corrects the orientation of alleles to match the forward strand. Proper harmonization is critical for ensuring that all variants are aligned correctly and ready for downstream analysis.","source":"@site/docs/Introduction/Harmonising-the-variants.mdx","sourceDirName":"Introduction","slug":"/Introduction/Harmonising-the-variants","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/Introduction/Harmonising-the-variants","draft":false,"unlisted":false,"editUrl":"https://github.com/EBISPOT/gwas-sumstats-harmoniser-documentation/tree/main/docs/Introduction/Harmonising-the-variants.mdx","tags":[],"version":"current","sidebarPosition":4,"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":4},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"Orientation of palindromic variants","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/Introduction/Orientation-of-palindromic-variants"},"next":{"title":"Quality control","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/Introduction/Quality-control"}},{"id":"Introduction/Orientation-of-palindromic-variants","title":"Orientation of palindromic variants","description":"Palindromic variants are genetic variants (such as A/T or G/C SNPs) that appear identical on both the forward and reverse DNA strands, making it difficult to distinguish their true orientation. To ensure that these variants are correctly aligned during harmonisation, the pipeline employs a method to infer their strand orientation using a strand consensus approach.","source":"@site/docs/Introduction/Orientation-of-palindromic-variants.md","sourceDirName":"Introduction","slug":"/Introduction/Orientation-of-palindromic-variants","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/Introduction/Orientation-of-palindromic-variants","draft":false,"unlisted":false,"editUrl":"https://github.com/EBISPOT/gwas-sumstats-harmoniser-documentation/tree/main/docs/Introduction/Orientation-of-palindromic-variants.md","tags":[],"version":"current","sidebarPosition":3,"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":3},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"Genome Build Mapping","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/Introduction/Genome-Build-Mapping"},"next":{"title":"Harmonising the variants","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/Introduction/Harmonising-the-variants"}},{"id":"Introduction/Overview","title":"Overview of the Harmonisation Pipeline","description":"The gwas-sumstats-harmoniser  is a pipeline designed to standardise variant data across different genome assemblies, ensuring consistency for downstream analysis. This process involves four key steps:","source":"@site/docs/Introduction/Overview.md","sourceDirName":"Introduction","slug":"/","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/","draft":false,"unlisted":false,"editUrl":"https://github.com/EBISPOT/gwas-sumstats-harmoniser-documentation/tree/main/docs/Introduction/Overview.md","tags":[],"version":"current","sidebarPosition":1,"frontMatter":{"slug":"/","sidebar_position":1},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"Introduction","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/category/introduction"},"next":{"title":"Genome Build Mapping","permalink":"/gwas_harmoniser_documentation/Introduction/Genome-Build-Mapping"}},{"id":"Introduction/Quality-control","title":"Quality control","description":"To ensure that only complete and reliable records are retained in the harmonised result, the final step of the pipeline is